Juillet 21, 2017



Part












NA continued to hold its stake in shares of Capital Trust, Inc. Egerton Capital Uk Llp sold 29,525 shares as Blackstone Mtg Tr Inc (BXMT)'s stock 0.00%. Envestnet Asset Management Inc.'s holdings in Capital Trust were worth $188,000 at the end of the most recent quarter.
A number of other large investors have also made changes to their positions in the stock. Advisory Services Network LLC purchased a new position in shares of Capital Trust during the first quarter worth $108,000. CAPROCK Group Inc. now owns 10,670 shares of the real estate investment trust's stock worth $330,000 after buying an additional 41 shares during the period. Narwhal Capital Management increased its stake in Capital Trust by 71.7% in the first quarter. Bank of America Corp DE now owns 1,141,887 shares of the real estate investment trust's stock valued at $35,353,000 after buying an additional 62,928 shares during the period.Parametric Portfolio Associates LLC raised its position in shares of Capital Trust, Inc.Investors wait Blackstone Mortgage Trust Inc (NYSE:BXMT) to report on July, 25 after the close. its quarterly earnings Wall Street analysts expect $0.58 EPS, down $0.04 or 6.45 % from last year's $0.62 same quarter earnings. Security National Trust Co. now owns 4,300 shares of the real estate investment trust's stock valued at $133,000 after buying an additional 2,300 shares during the last quarter. The Company conducts its operations as a real estate investment trust for the United States federal income tax purposes. Moreover, Shelton Cap Mgmt has 0.04% invested in Blackstone Mortgage Trust Inc (NYSE:BXMT) for 13,864 shares. The company has market cap of $1.18 billion. The stock has a 50-day moving average price of $31.51 and a 200 day moving average price of $30.99. Capital Trust, Inc. has a 52-week low of $27.89 and a 52-week high of $32.47.Capital Trust (NYSE:BXMT) last released its quarterly earnings data on Tuesday, April 25th. The real estate investment trust reported $0.55 earnings per share (EPS) for the quarter, missing analysts' consensus estimates of $0.63 by $0.08. Capital Trust had a net margin of 65.18% and a return on equity of 9.03%. The company's revenue was down 7.5% compared to the same quarter past year. The Geode Capital Management Llc holds 527,895 shares with $15.87 million value, up from 510,828 last quarter. Equities research analysts anticipate that Capital Trust, Inc. will post $2.54 EPS for the current year. Shareholders of record on Friday, June 30th were paid a $0.62 dividend. This represents a $2.48 annualized dividend and a yield of 7.99%. The ex-dividend date was Wednesday, June 28th. Capital Trust's payout ratio is presently 100.40%. The original version of this piece can be accessed at https://www.thestockobserver.com/2017/07/20/great-west-life-assurance-co-can-has-309000-position-in-capital-trust-inc-bxmt-updated-updated-updated-updated.html. Norges Bank acquired a new stake in Capital Trust during the fourth quarter worth $28,886,000. About shares traded. New York Community Bancorp, Inc. If you are reading this piece on another site, it was stolen and reposted in violation of global copyright legislation. Mraz Amerine & Associate invested 0.14% in Blackstone Mortgage Trust Inc (NYSE:BXMT).BXMT has been the subject of several research analyst reports. Zacks Investment Research raised Capital Trust from a "sell" rating to a "hold" rating in a report on Friday, April 14th. Finally, BidaskClub upgraded shares of Capital Trust from a "buy" rating to a "strong-buy" rating in a research report on Friday, June 16th. Keefe, Bruyette & Woods reissued an "outperform" rating on shares of Capital Trust in a report on Tuesday, July 4th. Finally, Deutsche Bank AG raised their price objective on shares of Capital Trust from $33.00 to $34.00 and gave the stock a "buy" rating in a research note on Friday, April 28th. One analyst has rated the stock with a sell rating, three have given a hold rating and four have assigned a buy rating to the stock. The company now has an average rating of "Hold" and a consensus target price of $32.50.Advantus Capital Management Inc decreased Blackstone Mortgage Trust Inc (BXMT) stake by 26.05% reported in 2016Q4 SEC filing. The Company originates and purchases senior loans collateralized by properties in North America and Europe. The company's investment programs focuses on loans and securities backed by commercial real estate assets.

 




