Trustmark Corporation is a bank holding company. The company has market cap of $2.17 billion. The Company’s principal subsidiary is Trustmark National Bank . It has a 19.29 P/E ratio. Through TNB and its subsidiaries, the Company operates as a financial services firm providing banking and other financial solutions.
The stock decreased 0.12% or $0.04 during the last trading session, reaching $32.11. About shares traded. Trustmark Corp (NASDAQ:TRMK) has risen 28.73% since July 19, 2016 and is uptrending. It has outperformed by 12.03% the S&P500.
Investors sentiment decreased to 1.01 in Q4 2016. Its down 0.24, from 1.25 in 2016Q3. It worsened, as 18 investors sold Trustmark Corp shares while 56 reduced holdings. 25 funds opened positions while 50 raised stakes. 42.70 million shares or 1.22% less from 43.23 million shares in 2016Q3 were reported. Blackrock Group Ltd has invested 0% in Trustmark Corp (NASDAQ:TRMK). Massachusetts-based Rhumbline Advisers has invested 0.01% in Trustmark Corp (NASDAQ:TRMK). Augustine Asset Mgmt stated it has 9,542 shares or 0.26% of all its holdings. Sg Americas Secs Ltd has 0% invested in Trustmark Corp (NASDAQ:TRMK). Moreover, Peak6 Limited Partnership has 0% invested in Trustmark Corp (NASDAQ:TRMK). Acadian Asset Management Llc holds 0% or 16,605 shares in its portfolio. Florida-based Dreman Value L L C has invested 0.01% in Trustmark Corp (NASDAQ:TRMK). Guernsey-based Airain Ltd has invested 0.03% in Trustmark Corp (NASDAQ:TRMK). Thompson Davis Communication Inc has 746 shares. Connor Clark And Lunn Limited reported 15,550 shares. Federated Investors Pa invested in 39,246 shares. Moreover, Ameriprise Finance has 0.01% invested in Trustmark Corp (NASDAQ:TRMK). 113,775 are held by Credit Suisse Ag. Toronto Dominion Retail Bank holds 7 shares or 0% of its portfolio. Renaissance Technologies Ltd Com reported 244,000 shares.








