					Full Description



Blackstone Mortgage Trust, Inc., incorporated on April 7, 1998, is a holding company. The Company conducts its operations as a real estate investment trust (REIT) for the United States federal income tax purposes. The Company originates and purchases senior loans collateralized by properties in North America and Europe. The Company originates and acquires commercial mortgage loans and related investments. The Company's business is focused on originating or acquiring senior, floating rate mortgage loans that are secured by a first priority mortgage on commercial real estate assets primarily in the office, lodging, retail, residential and industrial sectors. These investments may be in the form of whole loans or may also include pari passu participations within mortgage loans. It also originates and acquires fixed rate loans and subordinate loans, including subordinate mortgage interests and mezzanine loans. The Company's manager is BXMT Advisors L.L.C.The Company originates and purchases commercial real estate debt and related instruments to be held as long-term investments at amortized cost. It directly originates, co-originates and acquires debt instruments in conjunction with acquisitions, refinancings and recapitalizations of commercial real estate. In the case of loans, the Company acquires and focuses on performing loans that are supported by properties and portfolios. The Company's loan portfolio is diversified by collateral property type and geographic location, including senior mortgages and similar credit quality loans. The Company's various property types that secure loans in the Company's portfolio include office, hotel, retail, multifamily, manufactured housing, condominium and others. Its portfolio is focused on geographic locations, including the United States, the United Kingdom, Canada, Germany and the Netherlands.

» Full Overview of BXMT.N







